title.narrative: By 2021, government and CSO's have increased capacity at the national and subnational level for the provision of quality HIV treatment and care interventions for children and adolescents living with HIV especially in MINS

description.narrative: To build capacity of the national Ministry to lead the pediatric and adolescents' HIV programme as well as the capacity of health care workers, an in-depth data review was completed and a training manual for nurses updated to include the management of HIV in children and adolescents. Combined these are expected to contribute further to improved quality of HIV services. To reduce persistent barriers for adolescents living with HIV to access health services, UNICEF supported the Ministry of Health and CSOs to test a community-based service delivery model for adolescents to access antiretroviral medicines in their communities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
